        <h2 class="ecl-u-type-heading-2" id="inline-nav-4">
          Deviation List
        </h2>
        <p class="ecl-u-type-paragraph-m">
          EU Laissez-Passer issued to EU officials of German nationality may
          contain “wrong data in MRZ field”, depending on the date of
          issuance. The Nationality field contains the string “DEU”, as listed
          in the official ISO 3166 country code list maintained by ISO
          3166/MA, for all EU Laissez-Passer issued prior to 05/05/2022. Since
          then, all new EU Laissez-Passer issued to German nationals have the
          value “D&lt;&lt;” for the Nationality field, to make it consistent
          with the specification in ICAO Doc 9303 Part3.
        </p>

        <h2 class="ecl-u-type-heading-2" id="inline-nav-5">
          Contact Information
        </h2>
        <p class="ecl-u-type-paragraph-m">
          The main communication channel for the EU Laissez-Passer CSCA is
          email. Please use this email address only for issues related to the CSCA and not to the EU Laissez-Passer in
          general.
        </p>
        <p class="ecl-u-type-paragraph-m">
          The email address is:
          <a href="mailto:eu-csca@ec.europa.eu">eu-csca AT ec.europa.eu</a>.
          <br/>
          <br/>
          <br/>
          <br/>
        </p>
